news.title: Sagar Cements' net profit dips 59% to Rs 20.76 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 371.50 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 13 per cent from Rs 329.17 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat net profit dips 7% to Rs 214 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,622 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 11 per cent from Rs 2,353 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Spanish cabinet approves bill penalising empty homes, rewarding lower rents
news.para: Under the law, regional governments can declare areas as in "high demand" when the average household spends over 30% of its net income on rent or mortgage costs and bills and if property prices have risen more than 5% above inflation.

news.title: New homes sales jump 14% in US in September 2021
news.para: New home sales jumped 14.0% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 800,000 units last month, the highest level since March, the Commerce Department said on Tuesday.

news.title: PIL seeks appointment of Gujarat REAT's chairman, technical member
news.para: “Since the function of the tribunal is purely judicial and adjudicatory, keeping in view the doctrine of separation of powers…, the government ideally should have a minimal say in the functioning of the tribunal,” the plea said. “It is, however, manifest that ‘Administration of Justice’ is a subject matter of the Department of Justice under the Ministry of Law and Justice.”

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance posts net profit of Rs 18.8 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: ​Disbursements were better than the pre-pandemic levels at Rs 633 crore compared to Rs 517 crore in Q2FY21 and Rs 221 crore in Q1FY22, Ravi Subramanian, MD & CEO of the company said, adding asset quality improved with gross stage 3 assets improving by 36 bps to 1.72 per cent.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji in talks with global funds to set up $1.5 billion Investment Platforms
news.para: Each of these joint investment platforms will have equity funding of $500 million and will be investing close to $1 billion, including the leverage, in these real estate segments that are emerging as independent asset classes with strong growth potential, they said.

news.title: SC-monitored company issues list of Amrapali buyers who defaulted on payments
news.para: Name of close to 4,000 buyers have been made public on Wednesday and they are asked to submit details within 15 days.

news.title: hBits to buy Rs 18 crore office asset in Mumbai
news.para: hBits said the asset, located in Andheri East, is already leased to French firm Mane. The property will offer a rental yield of 10.04 per cent to the investors.

news.title: Protesters stall work at Noida airport site over rehabilitation demands
news.para: The protesters flocked to the site in Rohi village, where workers under a private contractor have been putting up a boundary wall. The villagers asked the workers to stop construction, threatening them with violence if they didn’t.

news.title: CERA Sanitaryware net profit up 89% to Rs 44 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 411.18 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 25 per cent from Rs 328.54 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Land hearings for second phase of Noida airport to start from Nov 1
news.para: Officials said the first meeting would be held in Mundhera on November 1. After a break for Diwali, the hearings will resume on November 8 and continue till the 11th.

news.title: Traders oppose North Delhi civic body's circular on property tax
news.para: “This circular is only applicable for a limited period from October 25 till March 31, 2022. This goes to show that it is only an eyewash to make a fool out of the traders before elections,” said Brijesh Goyal, chairman, CTI.

news.title: Drones to map 700 villages in Assam
news.para: There are around 22,724 villages in Assam, of which 700 had no maps so far and so posed hurdles in executing government projects and buying and selling of land.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to ease tax burden for illegal houses below 120 sqm
news.para: The officials had reported that some of the applications could not be granted building numbers legally owing to slight variations from permissible norms and such files were considered in the adalat.
